{
  "text": "The Chebyshev polynomials have frequently been used in numerical analysis including polynomial approximation, Gauss-quadrature integration, integral and differen-*Corresponding Author: Kourosh Parand: Department of Computer Sciences, Shahid Beheshti University, G.C., Tehran, Iran and Member of research group of Scientific Computing, Shahid Beheshti University, G.C., Tehran, Iran, E-mail: k_parand@sbu.ac.ir Mehdi Delkhosh: Department of Computer Sciences, Shahid Beheshti University, G.C., Tehran, Iran tial equations and spectral methods. Chebyshev polynomials have many properties, for example orthogonal, recursive, simple real roots, complete in the space of polynomials. For these reasons, many researchers have employed these polynomials in their research [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
